
DISCOM Test Utility for R-Car Gen3 based platforms

Description
===========

  discom_test is a test utility of DISCOM feature in libWFD library. Given an input JPEG/PNG image, the program will 
  decompress the image to RGBX8888 raw data, then calculate CRC32 value of raw data using CRC polynomial algorithm from 
  IEEE-802.3. After that, this CRC32 value will be compared with CRC32 calculated from DISCOM module. This program use 
  QNX libimg to decompress JPEG/PNG image. Please configure system to support libimg before running this program.

Options
=======
  --display -d
    Screen display ID of monitor that will be tested.

  --image -i
    Path of the image that will be calculated CRC32 (*.jpg, *.jpeg, *.png is accepted).

  --rect -r
    Image ROI that will be calculated CRC32, default ROI depend on DISCOM attached position:
      + input  - Image ROI is entire input image.
      + output - Image ROI is entire displayed image.

Example
=======
  1) Calculate CRC32 of entire given image
     $ discom_test --display=1 --image=/tmp/sample.jpg

  2) Calculate CRC32 of cropped region of given image
     $ discom_test --display=1 --image=/tmp/sample.jpg --rect=100,100,500,500
